# Trivy exception policy for PPCollection.
# Format: one Trivy ID (CVE / GHSA / etc.) per line, with optional `exp:`
# expiration date and a leading comment block describing why.
#
# Rules:
# - Scope to the exact CVE/package/path
# - Include business justification in a comment immediately above the ID
# - Include owner and expiration date
# - Remove entries once fixed

# Picomatch 4.0.0-4.0.3 method-injection + ReDoS, only present in the
# picomatch copy bundled inside @semantic-release/npm's `npm` CLI tarball
# at node_modules/npm/node_modules/tinyglobby/node_modules/picomatch. That
# npm CLI runs only in the CI release pipeline against package.json
# metadata and never matches user-supplied glob patterns. The host
# top-level picomatch is pinned to ^4.0.4 via package.json overrides.
# Re-evaluate by 2026-07-05. Owner: gogorichie.
# Listed by both CVE and GHSA IDs since Trivy 0.55 may report either.
CVE-2026-33672
CVE-2026-33671
GHSA-3v7f-55p6-f55p
GHSA-c2c7-rcm5-vvqj
